---
title: Salmon Banh Mi Baguettes with Spicy Slaw & Cucumber Spears
description: Tonight’s dinner features our spin on a Vietnamese banh mi sandwich with a twist from the sea: salmon! Quick-cooking, flavorful, and dressed with sweet Thai chili sauce, this fish makes a perfect sandwich-stuffer. It’s piled high with a spicy lime-spiked cabbage-cilantro slaw and loaded into toasty baguettes for a sammie experience you won’t forget any time soon. Top with a final squeeze of lime juice, serve crisp cucumber spears and extra slaw on the side, then prepare for total taste bud takeover (in just a quick 15 minutes!).
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/664caace5e4dc3c6a6a94104-86883711.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/686be399c0559753dc2eadb2-en-US.pdf
author: HelloFresh
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/salmon-banh-mi-baguettes-686be399c0559753dc2eadb2
servings: 2
course: main course
nutrition:
  calories: 810 kcal
  fat: 40 g
  saturated fat: 8 g
  carbohydrates: 55 g
  sugar: 14 g
  protein: 34 g
  fiber: 3 g
  sodium: 980 mg
time required: 15m
---

Pat @salmon{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and season all over with @salt{}
and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a large, preferably nonstick, pan over
medium-high heat. Add salmon to pan (skin sides down) and cook until skin is
crisp, ~{5-7%minutes}.

Flip and cook until cooked through, ~{1-2%minutes} more.

> While salmon cooks, move on to the rest of the recipe.

Once cooked, remove skin and discard; transfer salmon to a #medium bowl{}. Using
a #fork{}, break salmon into pieces. Stir in @sweet Thai chili sauce{1%ounce}.

Wash and dry produce.

Roughly chop @cilantro{1/4%ounce}. Quarter @lime{1}. Trim and quarter
@mini cucumber{1} lengthwise into spears.

In a second medium bowl, combine @coleslaw mix{4%ounce}, cilantro,
@mayonnaise{2%tablespoon}, @Sriracha{1%teaspoon}, a squeeze of lime juice
(big squeeze for 4 servings), salt, and pepper.

> For a brighter flavor, add more lime.

Halve and toast @demi-baguette{2} until golden; fill with salmon and as much
spicy slaw as you like.

Divide sandwiches between plates. Serve with cucumber spears and any remaining
spicy slaw on the side.

> Fish is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.